WEBVTT

1
00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:33.000
Your birthday present.

2
00:00:33.960 --> 00:00:36.400
- You already got me flowers.
- No. should have done better.

3
00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:40.040
If it's not too late. I'd like
to buy you some new perfume.

4
00:00:40.680 --> 00:00:43.680
- That's what you wanted. isn't it?
- Did Ilsa tell you that?

5
00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:47.360
I don't want to choose it for you.
You pick it out and I'll pay for it.

6
00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:49.840
Afterwards.
I'll take you to dinner.

7
00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:07.000
How do you know about
sheep diseases?

8
00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:09.640
Charlotte's family
kept sheep on Arran.

9
00:01:09.760 --> 00:01:11.360
It's probably a tax write-off.

10
00:01:11.960 --> 00:01:15.800
I spent a bit of time there before her
stepmom climbed into my bed.

11
00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:17.200
No.

12
00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:19.960
- What did you do?
- Well.

13
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.520
I really don't...
you don't have to tell me.

14
00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:26.120
- I didn't shag her.
- Oh. no.

15
00:01:26.280 --> 00:01:28.120
It was 1:00 in the morning.

16
00:01:28.200 --> 00:01:30.280
I jumped up.
I fell over the washstand.

17
00:01:30.520 --> 00:01:33.920
Charlotte ran in.
thought I'd keeled over pissed.

18
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.200
She started screaming and then Sir
Anthony came up in his dressing gown.

19
00:01:37.240 --> 00:01:39.280
but he hadn't done the belt right.

20
00:01:39.360 --> 00:01:41.440
You haven't truly experienced
the ruling classes

21
00:01:41.520 --> 00:01:45.120
until you've had a knight of the realm
shout at you with his cock hanging out.

22
00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:53.680
He collected stamps
and shotguns.

23
00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:56.000
And wives.
She was number three.

24
00:01:58.760 --> 00:01:59.760
What?

25
00:02:00.040 --> 00:02:04.040
Well. I mean.
I can't really talk. can I?

26
00:02:04.120 --> 00:02:06.080
I screwed up my marriage
in less than a year.

27
00:02:06.160 --> 00:02:08.760
You didn't screw it up.
Matthew had the affair.

28
00:02:08.840 --> 00:02:10.320
Yeah. but I...

29
00:02:12.280 --> 00:02:14.200
I never really
wanted to be there.

30
00:02:16.480 --> 00:02:19.880
You know. I tried to end it
on our honeymoon.

31
00:02:19.960 --> 00:02:21.120
It was just...

32
00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:25.600
It was all wrong. really.
but I chickened out.

33
00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:32.360
Anyway. people keep trying
to set me up.

34
00:02:34.680 --> 00:02:36.040
How's that going?

35
00:02:38.840 --> 00:02:40.000
It's not.

36
00:02:41.320 --> 00:02:42.360
None of them are--

37
00:03:02.920 --> 00:03:04.600
Sorry.
I still can't get used to heels.

38
00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:06.320
I struggle with them too.

39
00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:09.800
- I'll get you a taxi.
- No. you don't need to do that.

40
00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:11.280
- You spent way too much.
- You're doing OK.

41
00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:12.960
Look. that's down to you.

42
00:03:13.200 --> 00:03:14.640
It's the least I can do.

43
00:03:15.240 --> 00:03:16.800
I should do more.
Taxi!

44
00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:21.400
Strike. I...

45
00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:37.520
Night.

46
00:04:52.200 --> 00:04:54.800
The model was a redhead.
Elizabeth Siddal.

47
00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:56.200
Do you know about her?

48
00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:59.520
She married Rossetti.
got her heart broken.

49
00:05:01.040 --> 00:05:02.040
What do you see?

50
00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:09.240
I guess roses and nettles.

51
00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:13.400
It's like he's saying
love and pain belong together.

52
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:15.160
Yes.

53
00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:38.880
<i>Have you got an appointment?</i>

54
00:05:39.920 --> 00:05:42.560
<i>- No.</i>
<i>- We're strictly by appointment.</i>

55
00:05:42.640 --> 00:05:46.200
Then can I make an appointment
to see Robin Ellacott straight away?

56
00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:11.680
Daisies for innocence
and a willow tree for purity.

57
00:06:13.400 --> 00:06:15.680
It's Ophelia's whole story.

58
00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:46.480
Are you up to seeing someone?
I can tell her to come back.

59
00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.560
- Who is she?
- Her name's Edie Ledwell.

60
00:06:53.760 --> 00:06:54.800
Is she a nutter?

61
00:06:55.360 --> 00:06:56.800
Do you want me to ask her?

62
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.800
- Any kissing?
- He hasn't touched her.

63
00:07:22.880 --> 00:07:23.960
Maybe he's not interested.

64
00:07:24.080 --> 00:07:26.960
I don't think he's after her views
on pre-Raphaelite painters.

65
00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:30.760
So Midge.
how are you finding the job?

66
00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:33.640
Yeah. loving it. Plenty of fresh air.

67
00:07:34.480 --> 00:07:36.080
I'm due in Mayfair.

68
00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:39.600
Keep your camera ready.
If they kiss. it'll be one and done.

69
00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:45.560
Why isn't your name on the door?

70
00:07:45.920 --> 00:07:48.920
- The door was there before me.
- But you're here now.

71
00:07:50.200 --> 00:07:51.400
It's just a door.

72
00:07:52.120 --> 00:07:53.800
Look. I'm really sorry.

73
00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.240
I'm afraid if it's about a case.
we're not taking on any new clients.

74
00:07:57.320 --> 00:07:58.480
There's a waiting list.

75
00:07:59.280 --> 00:08:00.880
Can I smoke?

76
00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:03.520
It's a nonsmoking building.

77
00:08:04.080 --> 00:08:05.200
Well. somebody smokes.

78
00:08:05.840 --> 00:08:06.880
Not in office hours.

79
00:08:07.200 --> 00:08:10.600
It's fine. I've got gum.
And...

80
00:08:11.920 --> 00:08:13.640
That's for you.

81
00:08:15.800 --> 00:08:17.040
We're fully booked.

82
00:08:17.320 --> 00:08:19.880
Well. I can pay more
than your usual rate.

83
00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:22.240
Look. if I'm honest.
I'm totally desperate.

84
00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:24.760
so you can charge me
whatever you like.

85
00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:28.440
Can I at least tell you
what it is. please?

86
00:08:29.640 --> 00:08:30.920
I don't know what else to do.

87
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.320
- Do you want to take a seat?
- No.

88
00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:36.640
Have you heard of
the "Ink Black Heart"?

89
00:08:36.760 --> 00:08:39.640
- It's a TV show. isn't it?
- It is now.

90
00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:42.160
It started as a cartoon
we put on the web.

91
00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:44.120
Me and my ex-boyfriend made it.

92
00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:46.680
It's going to be a film soon.

93
00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:49.240
Sorry. I just really need...

94
00:08:49.920 --> 00:08:53.000
We've got a lot of fans
and most of them are great.

95
00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:54.960
but one of them is...
Oh. fuck it.

96
00:08:55.640 --> 00:08:57.240
Can I please have a cigarette?

97
00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:00.880
Yeah. you can have one
out the window.

98
00:09:21.760 --> 00:09:23.840
One of the fans
is stalking me online.

99
00:09:24.600 --> 00:09:26.840
And it's not because they like me.

100
00:09:27.160 --> 00:09:29.240
They completely hate me.

101
00:09:29.320 --> 00:09:32.680
It's like they've made it their mission
to make my life unbearable.

102
00:09:33.200 --> 00:09:37.200
I mean. I can handle the trolls.
but this is nothing like that.

103
00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:40.480
This has been every single day
for three years.

104
00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.840
- If it's stalking. then the police--
- I've already tried.

105
00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:47.680
They can't do anything because no one
knows this person's real name.

106
00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:50.840
They use the name Anomie
for all their accounts.

107
00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:53.800
Anomie was one of the creators
of an online game

108
00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:55.640
based on my cartoon.

109
00:09:58.200 --> 00:10:01.480
They've posted pictures of my flat.

110
00:10:02.160 --> 00:10:06.160
told people I used to work
as a prostitute. which isn't true.

111
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:10.400
They've even convinced Josh
that I'm Anomie.

112
00:10:10.480 --> 00:10:13.960
Like I'm harassing myself
just to get sympathy.

113
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:17.280
Josh is who I made the show with.

114
00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:20.160
This is someone I used to love

115
00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:24.520
and even he thinks
that I'm a scheming bitch.

116
00:10:27.400 --> 00:10:29.160
Everything is poisoned.

117
00:10:30.160 --> 00:10:32.520
And I feel like
I'm losing my mind.

118
00:10:33.840 --> 00:10:36.280
And you want to know what
the worst thing is?

119
00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:39.280
Anomie is someone who knows me.

120
00:10:39.800 --> 00:10:42.280
They know loads of stuff
and true things.

121
00:10:42.480 --> 00:10:44.840
like when
I tried to kill myself.

122
00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:46.520
- I'm so sorry.
- It's all right.

123
00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:49.280
Hardly anyone knew.
but Anomie did.

124
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:53.120
They knew which hospital I was in.
They tweeted it.

125
00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:55.520
Saying I'd done it for attention.

126
00:10:58.600 --> 00:11:01.800
I think I've covered everything.
It's all in the folder.

127
00:11:01.880 --> 00:11:04.320
I think there's a possibility

128
00:11:04.400 --> 00:11:07.600
it might be somebody I used
to live with. a guy called Pez.

129
00:11:07.960 --> 00:11:10.880
- Miss Ledwell--
- The point is I don't know.

130
00:11:10.960 --> 00:11:13.360
These people were my friends.
and...

131
00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:17.680
now I'm thinking. is it you?
Do you really hate me that much?

132
00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:19.680
Please help me.

133
00:11:21.200 --> 00:11:22.280
Look.

134
00:11:23.440 --> 00:11:28.080
Even if we were available. we just don't
have that kind of expertise.

135
00:11:29.120 --> 00:11:31.600
These agencies are
cyber specialists.

136
00:11:31.920 --> 00:11:33.000
They're both good.

137
00:11:33.520 --> 00:11:34.600
I...

138
00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:37.280
I really wanted it to be you.

139
00:11:37.840 --> 00:11:39.120
I've read about you.

140
00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:43.600
- Mr. Strike is very good at what he does.
- No. no. I wanted you.

141
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.320
But it's OK.

142
00:11:45.880 --> 00:11:47.360
I get it. You're too busy.

143
00:11:47.960 --> 00:11:48.960
So am I.

144
00:11:53.800 --> 00:11:57.440
- Is there really no chance at all?
- One of those agencies will help you.

145
00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:00.640
What happened to your neck?

146
00:12:01.200 --> 00:12:03.080
I'm just clumsy.

147
00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:10.840
That's two hours of the worst
conversation you'll ever hear.

148
00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:13.520
Right at the end.
he says he's got a flat in Chelsea.

149
00:12:14.040 --> 00:12:16.400
Can you ask the client if she
knows anything about that?

150
00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:17.960
- Will do.
- Thanks.

151
00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:22.600
I'm really sorry
we couldn't be of more help.

152
00:12:23.200 --> 00:12:24.200
Thanks.

153
00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:26.600
All right. well. bye. then.

154
00:12:28.400 --> 00:12:30.680
You should get this door fixed.

155
00:12:52.760 --> 00:12:57.440
<i>- Oh. my sister's going to a party.</i>
<i>- Why didn't she invite you?</i>

156
00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:00.880
<i>Because I'm dead. Because you've</i>
<i>eaten off all my skin and flesh.</i>

157
00:13:00.960 --> 00:13:04.760
<i>- It's not like you were using it.</i>
<i>- Sad. So very sad.</i>

158
00:13:05.080 --> 00:13:08.400
<i>Come on. Paperwhite. You're dead.</i>
<i>Things can only get better.</i>

159
00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:14.120
<i>Begone. foul thing!</i>

160
00:13:14.440 --> 00:13:15.680
<i>I'm not foul.</i>

161
00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:18.120
<i>Look at yourself.</i>
<i>A good heart is pink.</i>

162
00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:21.920
<i>- You are pickled in evil.</i>
<i>- Can we still play together?</i>

163
00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.840
<i>Yes.</i>
<i>Let's play a game. bwah.</i>

164
00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:26.960
<i>Drek wants to play.</i>

165
00:13:27.520 --> 00:13:30.840
Is that the "Ink Black Heart"?
Tell me you're not into that.

166
00:13:31.080 --> 00:13:33.400
- Why?
- My ex was obsessed.

167
00:13:33.840 --> 00:13:36.840
She used to do all the voices.
Sad. so very sad.

168
00:13:36.920 --> 00:13:39.520
Play the game. bwah.
Oh. shoot me now.

169
00:13:40.840 --> 00:13:42.760
The person who created it
just came in.

170
00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:44.880
What. Edie Ledwell?

171
00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:47.360
Yeah.
Did your ex talk about her as well?

172
00:13:47.440 --> 00:13:51.920
Oh. yeah. In Beth's world.
Edie Ledwell is a bigot. a phobe.

173
00:13:52.320 --> 00:13:54.200
a racist. a disablist.

174
00:13:54.440 --> 00:13:55.480
Is she. though?

175
00:13:56.000 --> 00:13:59.400
Probably not.
But Beth basically lives her life online.

176
00:13:59.480 --> 00:14:00.920
And you're not a true ally

177
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:03.920
unless you've burnt someone
at the stake before breakfast.

178
00:14:04.480 --> 00:14:06.040
She's left this in the loo.

179
00:14:06.440 --> 00:14:08.160
- Did she leave an address?
- No.

180
00:14:08.200 --> 00:14:10.440
And she's done it on purpose.
hasn't she?

181
00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:15.520
She's probably got an agent.
I'll get it back to her.

182
00:14:15.600 --> 00:14:18.480
- What? You're not taking her case?
- We can't. We've got no capacity.

183
00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:20.600
We most definitely do not.

184
00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:22.880
Keeping in the office like a teenager

185
00:14:22.960 --> 00:14:25.240
because you've been out
working so late.

186
00:14:25.320 --> 00:14:26.840
I'm agreeing with you.

187
00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:31.200
Do you know where
I'm supposed to be next?

188
00:14:31.240 --> 00:14:33.480
Petherton Road.
Infidelity.

189
00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:13.200
<i>So a couple of your fans</i>
<i>have created an online game</i>

190
00:15:13.240 --> 00:15:15.320
<i>based on one of your characters.</i>

191
00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:18.480
<i>Yeah. Drek's game.</i>
<i>We checked that out.</i>

192
00:15:18.560 --> 00:15:19.800
<i>The detail is unreal.</i>

193
00:15:20.240 --> 00:15:22.040
<i>Anomie and Morehouse.</i>
<i>thanks very much.</i>

194
00:15:23.560 --> 00:15:27.400
<i>It is weird. though.</i>
<i>because in our cartoon.</i>

195
00:15:27.480 --> 00:15:29.640
<i>Drek's game</i>
<i>isn't really a game.</i>

196
00:15:30.120 --> 00:15:32.800
<i>You know. the whole point is</i>
<i>that Drek makes up the rules</i>

197
00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:35.120
<i>as he goes along</i>
<i>so he can watch everyone lose.</i>

198
00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:37.240
<i>It's not a game</i>
<i>you can actually play.</i>

199
00:15:37.560 --> 00:15:40.280
<i>Anomie and Morehouse</i>
<i>don't seem to understand that.</i>

200
00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:08.200
Robin reckons that job
might be finished now.

201
00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:11.680
She could do the antiques job with you
if it still needs two people.

202
00:16:14.200 --> 00:16:16.200
Put her and Barclay on it.

203
00:16:16.680 --> 00:16:21.120
- Sam's doing the other thing in Chelsea.
- I'll take over on the Chelsea job.

204
00:16:30.080 --> 00:16:31.200
Thank you.

205
00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:32.600
- Allan Yeoman.
- Robin Ellacott.

206
00:16:32.920 --> 00:16:36.200
- I'm a private detective.
- Yes. Edie said she'd met you.

207
00:16:36.840 --> 00:16:38.160
Were you expecting me?

208
00:16:38.320 --> 00:16:40.200
Well. she did say that
if you happen to come by.

209
00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:41.920
that I might try
to change your mind.

210
00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:46.240
I did give her the names
of two digital specialists.

211
00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:49.360
I've called the ones you suggested.
Fingers crossed.

212
00:16:49.520 --> 00:16:51.760
Great. Here's her file.

213
00:16:52.440 --> 00:16:54.840
- Will you give Edie my best?
- One second.

214
00:16:56.400 --> 00:17:00.280
She left this for you on
the off chance you'd drop in.

215
00:17:01.520 --> 00:17:05.120
She didn't mean to waste your time.
She just had her heart set on you.

216
00:17:13.840 --> 00:17:17.800
Can I ask. why does Anomie
hate her so much?

217
00:17:18.280 --> 00:17:21.480
He's built an entire game
dedicated to her cartoon.

218
00:17:21.560 --> 00:17:24.360
I'd have thought she'd be his hero.

219
00:17:25.080 --> 00:17:27.760
All we can think of is
she once said in an interview

220
00:17:27.840 --> 00:17:31.960
she thought Drek's game didn't
understand Drek's character.

221
00:17:32.040 --> 00:17:33.920
I think I might have seen that.

222
00:17:34.000 --> 00:17:38.120
She said that Drek's games aren't really
games you can play in the cartoon.

223
00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:40.560
That's when the abuse
from Anomie started.

224
00:17:41.200 --> 00:17:43.200
Three years later. here we are.

225
00:17:44.440 --> 00:17:46.880
She's really been through hell.

226
00:17:46.960 --> 00:17:49.200
Her breakup with Josh was terrible.

227
00:17:49.280 --> 00:17:52.960
and now he's accused her of doing
all manner of nasty things.

228
00:17:53.040 --> 00:17:54.480
I've been very worried about her.

229
00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:02.320
Will you tell her that I watched the show
and I really liked it?

230
00:18:02.480 --> 00:18:04.240
She's very talented.

231
00:18:04.320 --> 00:18:07.080
She is.
And yes. I'll do that.

232
00:18:08.200 --> 00:18:09.200
Thank you.

233
00:18:09.680 --> 00:18:10.680
Take care.

234
00:18:11.760 --> 00:18:12.760
Bye.

235
00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:26.200
- Ilsa.
- Hello.

236
00:18:26.280 --> 00:18:27.360
Thanks for coming.

237
00:18:28.560 --> 00:18:30.000
I can't wait to show you this.

238
00:18:40.520 --> 00:18:42.560
- I'll wait outside.
- Thank you.

239
00:18:48.800 --> 00:18:52.600
And there's only one bedroom.
but I can get a sofa bed in here.

240
00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:55.200
I think it's great.

241
00:18:56.520 --> 00:18:58.760
What's the chain situation?

242
00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:01.960
There's no chain.
The landlord wants a quick sale. so.

243
00:19:02.120 --> 00:19:04.160
What does Cormoran think of it?

244
00:19:04.640 --> 00:19:06.480
I haven't told him yet.

245
00:19:09.640 --> 00:19:11.160
What's going on
with the two of you?

246
00:19:12.840 --> 00:19:15.320
What?
Well. I'll tell him at some point.

247
00:19:17.160 --> 00:19:18.800
Don't try to bullshit me.

248
00:19:19.360 --> 00:19:21.280
I've been a lawyer
since I was a fetus.

249
00:19:25.600 --> 00:19:31.240
Well. Cormoran took me out
for my birthday last month.

250
00:19:32.480 --> 00:19:34.640
And as I was leaving. he...

251
00:19:35.680 --> 00:19:36.880
went to kiss me.

252
00:19:37.840 --> 00:19:39.920
- Oh. my God.
- I just panicked.

253
00:19:40.600 --> 00:19:43.320
I kind of pulled away. And...

254
00:19:44.880 --> 00:19:46.680
I can still remember
the look on his face.

255
00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:52.320
He just sort of bundled me
into a taxi and that was that.

256
00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:55.680
I just panicked.

257
00:19:56.080 --> 00:19:57.080
Why?

258
00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:03.000
I don't know.

259
00:20:03.480 --> 00:20:04.800
Come on.

260
00:20:09.520 --> 00:20:10.800
Because...

261
00:20:12.480 --> 00:20:15.200
I knew he'd regret it
once he sobered up.

262
00:20:15.960 --> 00:20:19.360
And I couldn't stand

263
00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:23.240
the idea of hearing him say
that it was a mistake. I just...

264
00:20:25.520 --> 00:20:27.920
I just didn't want to hear him
say he hadn't meant it.

265
00:20:29.440 --> 00:20:32.000
So what are you saying?

266
00:20:34.040 --> 00:20:35.480
You in love with him?

267
00:20:41.320 --> 00:20:43.200
I definitely don't want to be.

268
00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:46.160
That'd screw everything up.

269
00:20:46.760 --> 00:20:48.320
You haven't talked about it?

270
00:20:51.160 --> 00:20:55.880
You know. the agency means a lot to me.
and I don't want to mess that up.

271
00:20:58.040 --> 00:21:01.040
Anyway. I've got a mortgage now.
so I need to focus on the job.

272
00:21:01.440 --> 00:21:03.320
It's exactly what he'd say.

273
00:21:23.400 --> 00:21:25.960
Can you bill eight hours
on the Fingers case?

274
00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:27.040
Thanks.

275
00:21:31.640 --> 00:21:32.640
Did you see that?

276
00:21:33.400 --> 00:21:35.320
He's come in with an overnight bag.

277
00:21:36.200 --> 00:21:38.240
Pat. I'm trying to concentrate.

278
00:21:38.320 --> 00:21:39.880
It's called success syndrome.

279
00:21:39.960 --> 00:21:43.200
Once all your bills are paid
and you're on top of your game.

280
00:21:43.800 --> 00:21:48.400
you start filling the void with booze
and unsuitable women and cigarettes.

281
00:21:53.280 --> 00:21:56.200
Isn't this the girl we had
in here a while back?

282
00:21:57.640 --> 00:21:59.200
Oh. Edie Ledwell. Yeah.

283
00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:02.400
Has her film been announced?

284
00:22:04.240 --> 00:22:06.240
No. love.
She's been murdered.

285
00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:26.560
Mr. Strike.

286
00:22:29.040 --> 00:22:30.200
Could you come in here?

287
00:22:54.480 --> 00:22:55.520
Thanks.

288
00:22:59.040 --> 00:23:00.760
Want something stronger?

289
00:23:01.280 --> 00:23:04.520
I don't want to talk
to the police smelling of booze.

290
00:23:06.520 --> 00:23:08.240
I'm fine. I...

291
00:23:09.520 --> 00:23:11.920
If I keeled over every time
someone was stabbed in London.

292
00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:14.240
I'd spend half my life unconscious.

293
00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:20.200
Her being killed had nothing to do
with us not taking the case.

294
00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:22.200
You know that. don't you?

295
00:23:25.320 --> 00:23:27.440
Yeah. obviously I know that.

296
00:23:33.600 --> 00:23:35.320
She was desperate. though.

297
00:23:42.240 --> 00:23:43.760
Can you just...

298
00:23:43.840 --> 00:23:46.480
Can you just give me a couple
minutes to get myself together?

299
00:24:00.600 --> 00:24:03.240
Evening. I'm DCI Richard Murphy.

300
00:24:03.640 --> 00:24:07.440
- This is Angela Darwish.
- Cormoran Strike. Head through there.

301
00:24:12.080 --> 00:24:17.040
- How are we spelling "Anomie"?
- A-N-O-M-I-E.

302
00:24:17.400 --> 00:24:20.640
It means a lack of usual ethical
and social standards.

303
00:24:20.880 --> 00:24:23.560
It can also mean feeling
disconnected from people.

304
00:24:24.200 --> 00:24:26.680
Edie wanted us to find out
who they were.

305
00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:28.880
She thought it was probably
someone close to her

306
00:24:28.960 --> 00:24:30.680
because when
she tried to kill herself.

307
00:24:30.880 --> 00:24:33.800
Anomie knew which hospital
she was sent to.

308
00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:36.520
She mentioned someone
she used to live with.

309
00:24:36.600 --> 00:24:38.680
Was that Wally Cardew?

310
00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:42.520
I think it was
someone called Pez. I think.

311
00:24:42.680 --> 00:24:45.400
I didn't take notes because
I knew we couldn't take the case.

312
00:24:45.960 --> 00:24:47.320
How was her state of mind?

313
00:24:47.920 --> 00:24:49.560
She was anxious.

314
00:24:50.320 --> 00:24:53.040
She needed to smoke.
She bit her fingernails.

315
00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:57.600
Her clothes were creased.
I mean. she had an expensive handbag.

316
00:24:57.680 --> 00:24:59.560
but her boots needed reheeling.

317
00:25:01.520 --> 00:25:04.640
And she had fingertip bruising
on her neck.

318
00:25:04.760 --> 00:25:07.600
I asked her about it.
She just made up an excuse.

319
00:25:09.520 --> 00:25:10.880
Was she in a relationship?

320
00:25:11.080 --> 00:25:13.840
She had a fiancé.
but he's not a suspect.

321
00:25:14.480 --> 00:25:18.120
Did she say anything about being
attacked for her political beliefs?

322
00:25:18.800 --> 00:25:20.960
She didn't mention politics. no.

323
00:25:22.400 --> 00:25:24.400
Well. unless
you've got anything.

324
00:25:24.680 --> 00:25:26.960
No. I think
we're all done here.

325
00:25:27.640 --> 00:25:30.280
Sorry.
Can I ask what happened?

326
00:25:30.880 --> 00:25:33.000
I know you're not allowed
to share anything officially.

327
00:25:33.120 --> 00:25:35.400
but we've got great
relationships with the police.

328
00:25:35.480 --> 00:25:37.160
and we're used
to confidentiality.

329
00:25:37.800 --> 00:25:39.440
I think that would be OK.

330
00:25:40.040 --> 00:25:44.200
She was due to meet a man called
Josh Blay in Highgate Cemetery.

331
00:25:44.280 --> 00:25:46.840
- Her ex-boyfriend.
- They were both attacked.

332
00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:49.840
We think she was already dead
before he arrived.

333
00:25:51.320 --> 00:25:54.120
Now. he's had surgery.
but he's still touch-and-go.

334
00:25:54.680 --> 00:25:55.680
Any witnesses?

335
00:25:55.800 --> 00:25:59.320
No. Nothing on cameras either.
Now. her phone was taken.

336
00:25:59.400 --> 00:26:02.280
so we're hoping they'll be
stupid enough to turn it on.

337
00:26:03.200 --> 00:26:05.360
I'm afraid that's all we can share.

338
00:26:06.680 --> 00:26:07.920
Thank you.

339
00:26:14.680 --> 00:26:16.920
I need to get hold of you.
where are you based?

340
00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:18.760
Everything goes through
DCI Murphy.

341
00:26:18.920 --> 00:26:20.920
Understood.
Thanks again.

342
00:26:46.120 --> 00:26:48.480
- Sorry. Do you mind?
- Beat me to it.

343
00:26:50.600 --> 00:26:54.200
Did you notice the way he's DCI Murphy
but she's just Angela Darwish?

344
00:26:54.640 --> 00:26:56.920
I asked how I could get hold
of her and she dodged it.

345
00:26:57.120 --> 00:26:58.240
What are you saying?

346
00:26:58.320 --> 00:26:59.960
I think she might be MI5.

347
00:27:00.120 --> 00:27:02.400
They work with the police
on counter-terrorism.

348
00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:07.160
Why would Edie Ledwell
be a target for terrorists?

349
00:27:07.200 --> 00:27:10.920
I don't know. They did ask
about her politics. didn't they?

350
00:27:11.200 --> 00:27:13.840
And that guy they mentioned.
Wally Cardew.

351
00:27:13.920 --> 00:27:18.200
used to voice a character on her cartoon.
but she sacked him for being alt-right.

352
00:27:22.760 --> 00:27:26.880
It's not our case. though. is it?
So we're wasting our time.

353
00:27:30.120 --> 00:27:31.880
I'm going to go home.

354
00:27:57.880 --> 00:27:58.880
See you.

355
00:28:46.960 --> 00:28:48.120
<i>Where do we start?</i>

356
00:28:48.480 --> 00:28:51.520
<i>- Well. you know where we started.</i>
<i>- Yeah. I'm talking about for this.</i>

357
00:28:51.880 --> 00:28:54.280
<i>Where do we start?</i>

358
00:28:54.760 --> 00:28:57.280
<i>Talk about your plans</i>
<i>for world domination.</i>

359
00:28:57.520 --> 00:28:58.640
<i>That's a given.</i>

360
00:28:58.760 --> 00:29:02.080
<i>Katya. what do you reckon?</i>
<i>Katya is our media mastermind.</i>

361
00:29:02.280 --> 00:29:04.200
<i>So this video is all her fault?</i>

362
00:29:04.800 --> 00:29:08.640
<i>Edie and Josh. you're two episodes in.</i>
<i>You've had a great reaction.</i>

363
00:29:08.960 --> 00:29:10.120
<i>What do you want to say</i>
<i>to all the people</i>

364
00:29:10.200 --> 00:29:12.600
<i>who've discovered</i>
<i>the "Ink Black Heart"?</i>

365
00:29:13.160 --> 00:29:15.880
<i>- Thank you?</i>
<i>- Don't make it sound like a question.</i>

366
00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:18.200
<i>It's like you're not sure</i>
<i>if you should give a shit.</i>

367
00:29:18.280 --> 00:29:19.760
<i>Should I?</i>

368
00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:24.840
<i>Thank you for watching.</i>
<i>We really appreciate it a lot.</i>

369
00:29:29.200 --> 00:29:32.680
<i>So I got fired from playing</i>
<i>Drek because I made some jokes.</i>

370
00:29:32.800 --> 00:29:34.000
<i>Process that.</i>

371
00:29:34.400 --> 00:29:38.200
<i>A comedy cartoon fires me</i>
<i>for doing comedy sketches.</i>

372
00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:43.080
<i>Did I pick on disabled people?</i>
<i>No. I went for everyone.</i>

373
00:29:43.480 --> 00:29:45.240
<i>And I wasn't even going for them.</i>

374
00:29:45.320 --> 00:29:50.040
<i>I was going for the kind of idiots</i>
<i>that fire people like me over "values."</i>

375
00:29:51.880 --> 00:29:53.960
<i>I mean. what values are</i>
<i>we talking about. Edie?</i>

376
00:29:54.040 --> 00:29:55.640
<i>Because we all know your values.</i>

377
00:29:55.760 --> 00:29:58.560
<i>Shagging other people's boyfriends.</i>
<i>nicking other people's ideas.</i>

378
00:29:58.880 --> 00:30:00.560
<i>Are they values? I don't know.</i>

379
00:30:01.000 --> 00:30:03.000
<i>Ask Kea Niven maybe.</i>

380
00:30:03.840 --> 00:30:06.840
<i>Where did the inspiration</i>
<i>for Harty come from?</i>

381
00:30:08.040 --> 00:30:12.040
<i>Well. when I was a kid. my mum told me</i>
<i>this story about this evil person</i>

382
00:30:12.120 --> 00:30:14.560
<i>who swapped their heart for a stone</i>

383
00:30:14.920 --> 00:30:18.400
<i>so they wouldn't have to feel any</i>
<i>remorse for the things they'd done.</i>

384
00:30:19.000 --> 00:30:21.880
<i>And then we were</i>
<i>in the cemetery one day</i>

385
00:30:21.960 --> 00:30:25.240
<i>and I had this idea</i>
<i>that maybe the heart lived on</i>

386
00:30:25.680 --> 00:30:27.760
<i>after the evil man was buried.</i>

387
00:30:28.280 --> 00:30:30.960
<i>But it's turned black</i>
<i>'cause he's pickled in evil.</i>

388
00:30:31.160 --> 00:30:33.560
<i>Oh. but he's not really evil. though.</i>

389
00:30:33.640 --> 00:30:37.120
<i>It's just no one will believe him</i>
<i>because of who his owner was.</i>

390
00:30:39.160 --> 00:30:40.200
Thank you.

391
00:30:42.560 --> 00:30:43.840
<i>What's up. everyone?</i>

392
00:30:44.520 --> 00:30:45.960
<i>Can't say "bwah" anymore</i>

393
00:30:46.080 --> 00:30:49.080
<i>because apparently.</i>
<i>that's copyright infringement.</i>

394
00:30:49.160 --> 00:30:51.320
<i>Even though me saying</i>
<i>it that exact same way</i>

395
00:30:51.520 --> 00:30:54.200
<i>is where Edie got the idea</i>
<i>for Drek's voice in the first place.</i>

396
00:30:54.280 --> 00:30:55.280
<i>Mental.</i>

397
00:30:56.800 --> 00:30:58.040
<i>Can't get any auditions</i>

398
00:30:58.160 --> 00:31:02.680
<i>because Edie fired me for being</i>
<i>whatever. racist. disablist.</i>

399
00:31:03.240 --> 00:31:04.680
<i>No one will touch me.</i>

400
00:31:06.440 --> 00:31:08.400
<i>So she didn't just get me</i>
<i>fired from one job.</i>

401
00:31:08.480 --> 00:31:10.960
<i>She got me fired</i>
<i>from the whole industry.</i>

402
00:31:12.280 --> 00:31:13.280
<i>So this is me now.</i>

403
00:31:15.640 --> 00:31:17.360
<i>I'm going to do me own thing.</i>

404
00:31:18.480 --> 00:31:21.480
<i>Just me and you guys.</i>
<i>going direct.</i>

405
00:31:23.200 --> 00:31:24.920
<i>No mainstream media required.</i>

406
00:31:27.240 --> 00:31:32.160
<i>Mali and Nigeria. they were</i>
<i>all minting it. selling African slaves.</i>

407
00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:38.040
<i>And then the Royal Navy shut down</i>
<i>their business and they're furious.</i>

408
00:31:38.120 --> 00:31:43.000
{\an8}<i>The Navy lost 17.000 men</i>
<i>freeing 150.000 slaves.</i>

409
00:31:44.120 --> 00:31:45.880
{\an8}<i>That's called paying a price.</i>

410
00:31:46.280 --> 00:31:49.120
{\an8}<i>But this lot. they don't</i>
<i>want to hear about that.</i>

411
00:31:49.240 --> 00:31:53.680
{\an8}<i>No. they're like. aw. they</i>
<i>blew all their slave money.</i>

412
00:31:53.800 --> 00:31:56.800
{\an8}<i>And then we stopped them</i>
<i>from selling human beings.</i>

413
00:31:57.120 --> 00:31:59.680
{\an8}<i>and so we need to give them</i>
<i>some more money.</i>

414
00:31:59.880 --> 00:32:01.280
{\an8}<i>And I'm like. why?</i>

415
00:32:02.040 --> 00:32:04.080
{\an8}<i>Instead of calling for reparations.</i>

416
00:32:04.160 --> 00:32:07.960
{\an8}<i>how about sending the Royal Navy</i>
<i>a thank you note instead?</i>

417
00:32:10.320 --> 00:32:12.200
{\an8}<i>I'm going to be doing</i>
<i>some more pranks later on.</i>

418
00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:14.680
{\an8}<i>Come down and say hello.</i>
<i>Details in my socials.</i>

419
00:32:15.040 --> 00:32:17.240
{\an8}<i>Play the game. bwah.</i>

420
00:32:35.160 --> 00:32:39.480
<i>Next question from the fans.</i>
<i>from Lepine's Disciple.</i>

421
00:32:41.120 --> 00:32:42.920
<i>Are you guys a couple?</i>

422
00:32:47.200 --> 00:32:48.200
<i>Yeah.</i>

423
00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:49.320
<i>No spoilers.</i>

424
00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:51.400
<i>Are you saying</i>
<i>you know how it ends?</i>

425
00:32:51.480 --> 00:32:52.920
<i>It has to end badly.</i>

426
00:32:53.360 --> 00:32:55.640
<i>Or in a haze of drink and drugs.</i>

427
00:32:56.320 --> 00:32:57.680
<i>No. that's now.</i>

428
00:33:00.200 --> 00:33:01.640
<i>These are the good times.</i>

429
00:33:10.120 --> 00:33:11.120
Yeah. I'll leave them at home.

430
00:33:11.800 --> 00:33:14.640
I'll ring you back.
Yeah. yeah.

431
00:33:18.680 --> 00:33:19.840
- Oh. hey.
- Hi.

432
00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:23.200
I wanted to update you on Edie Ledwell.
In the strictest confidence. of course.

433
00:33:23.280 --> 00:33:24.840
Great. Thank you.
Do you want to come up?

434
00:33:24.960 --> 00:33:27.040
No. no. no. That's OK.
I need to be getting back.

435
00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:28.160
OK.

436
00:33:28.400 --> 00:33:31.000
There's going to be
an article in the papers.

437
00:33:31.200 --> 00:33:33.640
It'll say that a far-right group
called The Halvening

438
00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:37.480
are claiming responsibility
for the murder of Edie Ledwell

439
00:33:37.560 --> 00:33:40.640
along with pipe bombs being
sent to three female MPs.

440
00:33:40.800 --> 00:33:43.840
I mean. the journalist says it's come
from one source done over email.

441
00:33:43.960 --> 00:33:47.160
but we've been following this lot
for several months

442
00:33:47.200 --> 00:33:50.240
and everything they've told
the journalists looks credible.

443
00:33:51.360 --> 00:33:53.080
Have you got anything else
on Anomie?

444
00:33:53.360 --> 00:33:57.480
We had a look and he spent a lot of time
and effort trying to tear Edie down.

445
00:33:57.560 --> 00:33:59.480
which fits with one
of the Halvening's strategies.

446
00:33:59.560 --> 00:34:01.360
But this game he created--

447
00:34:01.440 --> 00:34:04.200
- Drek's game.
- Yeah. It's been running for three years.

448
00:34:04.240 --> 00:34:07.040
I don't see the Halvening
bothering to build a whole game

449
00:34:07.120 --> 00:34:08.760
just to go after one target.

450
00:34:09.160 --> 00:34:10.400
Well. apart from what's in this article.

451
00:34:10.480 --> 00:34:13.240
is there any evidence that
the Halvening killed Edie?

452
00:34:13.320 --> 00:34:16.600
Well. we know the killer used
a taser on Edie and Josh.

453
00:34:16.680 --> 00:34:18.440
And according to
the journalist's source.

454
00:34:18.520 --> 00:34:21.200
the Halvening use Bitcoin
to get their kit off the dark web.

455
00:34:21.280 --> 00:34:25.680
things like high-quality latex disguises
and materials for making bombs.

456
00:34:25.800 --> 00:34:27.480
Using a taser fits with that.

457
00:34:28.080 --> 00:34:30.040
- Why have they gone public now?
- Don't know.

458
00:34:30.360 --> 00:34:32.320
Maybe one of them
grew a conscience.

459
00:34:32.400 --> 00:34:33.800
Or they might have decided

460
00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:36.960
that now it's time to start taking
credit for what they've done.

461
00:34:37.440 --> 00:34:38.680
It's hard to tell.

462
00:34:38.840 --> 00:34:41.800
We've got a big team working
on all of this.

463
00:34:42.320 --> 00:34:45.760
- I just thought you'd want to know.
- Thank you. I really appreciate it.

464
00:34:45.840 --> 00:34:48.520
It's nice seeing you again.

465
00:34:49.640 --> 00:34:50.800
You too.

466
00:35:01.880 --> 00:35:03.760
Strike and Ellacott Agency.

467
00:35:05.320 --> 00:35:06.560
One moment.

468
00:35:08.080 --> 00:35:09.640
Allan Yeoman for you.

469
00:35:13.240 --> 00:35:15.240
Mr. Yeoman.
I've been meaning to call you.

470
00:35:15.480 --> 00:35:17.880
<i>- Hi.</i>
<i>- I am so sorry to hear about Edie.</i>

471
00:35:17.960 --> 00:35:20.080
I wish we'd been able to help.

472
00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:23.520
<i>You might still be able to.</i>
<i>Would you consider meeting me?</i>

473
00:35:25.400 --> 00:35:27.240
Yeah. of course we would.

474
00:35:30.640 --> 00:35:32.480
Good to see you again.
Ms. Ellacott.

475
00:35:32.560 --> 00:35:34.840
I'm Allan Yeoman.
I represented Edie Ledwell.

476
00:35:34.920 --> 00:35:37.080
This is Richard Elgar.
the head of Maverick Films.

477
00:35:37.600 --> 00:35:40.200
His company will be making
the "Ink Black Heart" film.

478
00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:42.320
Don't let my accent throw you off.

479
00:35:42.440 --> 00:35:43.800
We're a British company.

480
00:35:44.360 --> 00:35:46.640
This is Edie's uncle. Grant Ledwell.

481
00:35:47.120 --> 00:35:48.480
- Her next of kin.
- Hello.

482
00:35:48.560 --> 00:35:50.240
We thought
we should include him.

483
00:35:50.600 --> 00:35:53.240
I've taken on managing Edie's
share of the "Ink Black Heart."

484
00:35:53.680 --> 00:35:54.920
- Sorry for your loss.
- Thank you.

485
00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:56.560
Please sit down.

486
00:35:57.040 --> 00:35:59.880
Have you heard anything more
from the police investigation?

487
00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:05.680
They reckon it's far-right nutters angry
about Wally Cardew getting fired.

488
00:36:06.280 --> 00:36:09.240
- Have you seen the papers?
- We read the article. yeah.

489
00:36:09.320 --> 00:36:11.400
What about Josh Blay?
How is he?

490
00:36:12.280 --> 00:36:17.200
I've spoken to Katya Upcott a few times.
She's Josh's agent. They're very close.

491
00:36:17.240 --> 00:36:21.000
Josh is partially paralyzed.
I don't think he remembers very much.

492
00:36:21.080 --> 00:36:24.840
- I wouldn't rely on Josh Blay.
- Why do you say that?

493
00:36:24.920 --> 00:36:27.800
I'm just saying that he's the only one who
benefits from all this. isn't he?

494
00:36:27.880 --> 00:36:31.280
He's the only creator left.
He's not the only Ledwell. though.

495
00:36:31.360 --> 00:36:34.440
If the knife had gone 2 millimeters
to the left. he'd have been killed.

496
00:36:34.520 --> 00:36:36.840
I don't think anyone
believes Josh is a suspect.

497
00:36:37.240 --> 00:36:41.480
We should say that making this film
is absolutely in Josh's best interests.

498
00:36:41.560 --> 00:36:43.760
The cost of his ongoing care
is going to be significant.

499
00:36:43.840 --> 00:36:46.280
I think
he treated Edie very badly.

500
00:36:46.360 --> 00:36:49.600
Guys. if I may. we should
let the police do their job.

501
00:36:50.200 --> 00:36:52.200
We're here to discuss the film.

502
00:36:52.600 --> 00:36:55.200
Well. exactly.
We can't sit here all day.

503
00:36:55.240 --> 00:37:00.200
OK. so what we'd like you to
do is find out who Anomie is.

504
00:37:00.280 --> 00:37:02.320
He's the creator of Drek's game.

505
00:37:02.680 --> 00:37:04.400
I thought there were two creators.

506
00:37:04.480 --> 00:37:08.480
Sure. but the other guy. Morehouse.
he's never been a problem.

507
00:37:08.560 --> 00:37:11.200
Anomie is jeopardizing our movie.

508
00:37:11.800 --> 00:37:15.280
Just before Edie died.
we were about to close the film deal.

509
00:37:16.480 --> 00:37:19.480
Now. as Edie's heir. Grant can sign.

510
00:37:19.840 --> 00:37:23.040
But as things stand.
Josh won't go ahead.

511
00:37:23.880 --> 00:37:27.920
- Not while Anomie is still active.
- Josh just wants more money.

512
00:37:28.000 --> 00:37:30.440
Josh knows how
vicious Anomie can be.

513
00:37:30.520 --> 00:37:32.400
He's worried Anomie
will turn his sights on him.

514
00:37:32.480 --> 00:37:36.080
No. it's me Anomie's targeting.
He's coming after me already.

515
00:37:36.160 --> 00:37:38.240
What kind of things is he doing?

516
00:37:38.320 --> 00:37:41.320
Well. saying stuff like
me and Heather started as an affair.

517
00:37:41.520 --> 00:37:42.520
Is that true?

518
00:37:42.880 --> 00:37:47.280
I'm not prying. I just want to know
if Anomie's information is accurate.

519
00:37:47.360 --> 00:37:50.680
Well. my first marriage was
over in all but name.

520
00:37:50.800 --> 00:37:53.680
But there's other stuff. like
knowing my ex-wife has lupus.

521
00:37:53.960 --> 00:37:56.640
He's hostile to anyone
involved in the film project.

522
00:37:57.080 --> 00:38:00.800
And if he continues like this.
he's going to toxify the entire brand.

523
00:38:00.880 --> 00:38:03.280
No. but he's not hostile
to Josh. though. is he?

524
00:38:03.360 --> 00:38:04.920
Always leaves Josh alone.

525
00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:08.080
Now. this film is supposed
to be a no-brainer.

526
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:10.080
but now we've got Josh holding out

527
00:38:10.160 --> 00:38:13.200
and we've got Edie's fiancé.
who's trying to get paid for a script--

528
00:38:13.280 --> 00:38:14.600
That's not relevant here.

529
00:38:15.240 --> 00:38:17.200
Who is Edie's fiancé?

530
00:38:17.640 --> 00:38:19.920
Some bloke called Phillip Ormond.
He's a total chancer.

531
00:38:20.480 --> 00:38:24.680
Find out who Anomie is so we
can get Josh to sign the deal.

532
00:38:24.800 --> 00:38:27.160
That's what we're hoping
you will do for us.

533
00:38:27.200 --> 00:38:30.160
We tried the cyber route you suggested.
but it went nowhere.

534
00:38:30.680 --> 00:38:32.920
Security around the game is top-notch.

535
00:38:33.360 --> 00:38:34.400
We need a new approach.

536
00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:37.920
Can I just ask. were gaming
rights part of the film deal?

537
00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:39.480
Yeah. and they still are.

538
00:38:39.840 --> 00:38:42.600
So could you shut down Drek's
game on the basis of copyright

539
00:38:42.680 --> 00:38:44.520
and go after Anomie that way?

540
00:38:44.600 --> 00:38:46.600
He hasn't monetized his game.

541
00:38:46.880 --> 00:38:50.200
so it would be hard to make
the case for financial loss.

542
00:38:50.960 --> 00:38:54.280
And since we don't have
a real person to take to court--

543
00:38:55.000 --> 00:38:57.600
Quite.
We need Anomie's real name.

544
00:38:59.160 --> 00:39:02.200
How under the radar are
you planning on being?

545
00:39:02.360 --> 00:39:03.680
We want to be discreet.

546
00:39:03.880 --> 00:39:06.000
Josh's agent knows what we're doing
and she's supportive.

547
00:39:06.080 --> 00:39:08.120
so you can talk to Katya.

548
00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:10.880
Maybe Josh as well.
provided he's up to it.

549
00:39:12.520 --> 00:39:16.360
You were Edie's first choice.
and I think with good reason.

550
00:39:17.120 --> 00:39:18.120
So...

551
00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:20.560
Do you think you might
be able to help us?

552
00:39:20.640 --> 00:39:22.160
Absolutely.

553
00:39:22.200 --> 00:39:23.360
Unless?

554
00:39:23.600 --> 00:39:24.680
I'm in.

555
00:39:29.360 --> 00:39:30.360
Thank you.

556
00:39:34.240 --> 00:39:35.680
I have one question.

557
00:39:36.440 --> 00:39:38.200
We find out who Anomie is.

558
00:39:39.080 --> 00:39:40.640
what do you plan to do about it?

559
00:39:41.080 --> 00:39:42.320
Once we have a name.

560
00:39:42.600 --> 00:39:46.320
it shouldn't be hard to turn Anomie
from hunter to hunted.

561
00:39:47.240 --> 00:39:49.360
We'll find evidence of hypocrisy.

562
00:39:49.800 --> 00:39:52.760
racial insensitivity.
sexual harassment.

563
00:39:53.360 --> 00:39:54.920
There's always something.

564
00:39:55.000 --> 00:39:56.200
We'll put it out there.

565
00:39:56.840 --> 00:40:00.160
Those who live by the mob
die by the mob.

566
00:40:03.040 --> 00:40:04.040
Thank you.

567
00:40:04.760 --> 00:40:06.040
We'll get started.

568
00:40:09.960 --> 00:40:13.600
Edie was convinced that Anomie
was someone who knew her.

569
00:40:13.680 --> 00:40:16.760
She tried to figure it out herself
by looking at Anomie's tweets.

570
00:40:17.120 --> 00:40:19.240
When Edie attempted suicide.

571
00:40:19.400 --> 00:40:22.080
Anomie knew about it
within hours of it happening.

572
00:40:22.160 --> 00:40:24.680
And likewise. when they were
in talks about a feature film.

573
00:40:24.800 --> 00:40:27.600
Anomie already knew which production
company was involved.

574
00:40:27.920 --> 00:40:31.800
So Anomie is obviously someone
with access to inside information.

575
00:40:32.400 --> 00:40:36.280
Now. this first group of suspects are
people that Josh and Edie worked with.

576
00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:40.240
Most of them still live together in
an artists' collective up in Highgate.

577
00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:42.320
Would you do the lights. Midge?

578
00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:46.400
<i>- Haze of drink and drugs.</i>
<i>- Nah. that's now.</i>

579
00:40:47.680 --> 00:40:49.160
<i>These are the good times.</i>

580
00:40:50.680 --> 00:40:52.280
<i>We're not doing this on our own.</i>

581
00:40:52.760 --> 00:40:55.600
<i>North Grove Collective. say hello.</i>

582
00:40:57.160 --> 00:41:00.600
<i>Nils is not just our landlord</i>
<i>and an artist in his own right.</i>

583
00:41:00.840 --> 00:41:02.440
<i>but today he's also our cameraman.</i>

584
00:41:02.520 --> 00:41:04.520
<i>Yeah. this is too many jobs.</i>

585
00:41:04.640 --> 00:41:09.040
That is Nils De Jung.
He owns the building they live in.

586
00:41:11.800 --> 00:41:13.840
<i>It's Pez Pierce.</i>
<i>ladies and gentlemen.</i>

587
00:41:13.920 --> 00:41:15.920
<i>Though it's mostly the ladies</i>
<i>I'm talking to now.</i>

588
00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:21.200
And this guy is who Edie
told me was her main suspect.

589
00:41:22.560 --> 00:41:24.880
<i>Cheers. girls.</i>
<i>Swing by anytime.</i>

590
00:41:25.400 --> 00:41:27.000
<i>Tell them who you play.</i>

591
00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:30.600
<i>I play Magspie.</i>
<i>a thieving magpie.</i>

592
00:41:30.680 --> 00:41:33.880
<i>And the fact that I'm a Scouser</i>
<i>is purely coincidental.</i>

593
00:41:34.240 --> 00:41:36.000
<i>But if this interview</i>
<i>ever goes missing. though.</i>

594
00:41:36.080 --> 00:41:39.240
<i>That'll be because it was too shite</i>
<i>to even go on the internet.</i>

595
00:41:41.360 --> 00:41:43.760
<i>- You've done me already.</i>
<i>- Yeah. take a bow.</i>

596
00:41:43.840 --> 00:41:46.520
Now. this is Katya Upcott.

597
00:41:46.640 --> 00:41:50.320
She started out helping them with PR
and ended up as their agent.

598
00:41:50.440 --> 00:41:52.520
Edie moved on.
but Josh stayed with her.

599
00:41:52.840 --> 00:41:55.600
She had access to all
their deal negotiations.

600
00:41:58.320 --> 00:41:59.480
<i>Wait. why am I last?</i>

601
00:42:00.320 --> 00:42:03.160
<i>Main event. mate.</i>
<i>Headliner always comes on last.</i>

602
00:42:03.520 --> 00:42:06.920
<i>That's right. bwah.</i>
<i>'Cause it's all about Drek.</i>

603
00:42:07.400 --> 00:42:09.360
<i>You mean it's all about Wally.</i>

604
00:42:09.440 --> 00:42:12.000
<i>Play the game. bwah.</i>

605
00:42:12.960 --> 00:42:15.600
Wally Cardew is someone the police
were already interested in

606
00:42:15.760 --> 00:42:17.480
as a suspect in Edie's murder.

607
00:42:18.360 --> 00:42:20.760
I've looked at the comments
section on his video channel.

608
00:42:20.840 --> 00:42:24.800
It's full of people urging him to check
out the Brotherhood of Ultima Thule.

609
00:42:24.920 --> 00:42:27.680
- What's that?
- They're an alt-right movement.

610
00:42:27.800 --> 00:42:30.560
They reckon they're
reviving Viking ideals.

611
00:42:31.080 --> 00:42:32.280
I'm not sure the original Vikings

612
00:42:32.360 --> 00:42:35.760
were that bothered about
feminists or racial purity.

613
00:42:37.360 --> 00:42:40.120
I'm thinking they might be a feeder group
for the Halvening.

614
00:42:40.240 --> 00:42:42.960
who've claimed responsibility
for Edie's murder.

615
00:42:43.560 --> 00:42:47.520
North Grove offer evening art classes.
which anyone can sign up for.

616
00:42:47.600 --> 00:42:50.200
so I have enrolled
in a class with Mariam.

617
00:42:50.240 --> 00:42:53.360
who is married to Nils.
so I'll be watching Nils and Pez.

618
00:42:53.480 --> 00:42:54.960
You're doing Venetia Hall again?

619
00:42:55.040 --> 00:42:58.320
No. I am Jessica.
marketing executive

620
00:42:58.400 --> 00:43:00.960
who's always regretted
dropping A-level art.

621
00:43:01.880 --> 00:43:03.560
And what about the others?

622
00:43:03.760 --> 00:43:06.800
So this is Kea Niven.
Josh's ex-girlfriend.

623
00:43:06.880 --> 00:43:11.000
And Yasmin Weatherhead
is a PA that Edie fired.

624
00:43:11.080 --> 00:43:15.040
Edie ended up discounting both of them
because when Josh broke up with Kea.

625
00:43:15.120 --> 00:43:17.320
she no longer had access
to inside information.

626
00:43:17.400 --> 00:43:19.360
and the same goes for Yasmin.

627
00:43:19.760 --> 00:43:22.880
They're not ruled out as Anomie.
They're just low priority.

628
00:43:23.800 --> 00:43:25.480
And Yasmin's a writer?

629
00:43:25.800 --> 00:43:29.120
She's writing a book about
being an "Ink Black Heart" fan.

630
00:43:29.360 --> 00:43:31.520
Oh. that's
my holiday reading sorted.

631
00:43:31.800 --> 00:43:34.520
The last one we've added is not someone
Edie had as a suspect.

632
00:43:34.640 --> 00:43:36.360
Phillip Ormond. her fiancé.

633
00:43:36.680 --> 00:43:40.800
Ormond lived with Edie. so he had
access to personal information.

634
00:43:41.360 --> 00:43:45.080
She also had bruising on her neck.
which she avoided talking about.

635
00:43:45.280 --> 00:43:47.360
so we definitely need to watch him.

636
00:43:47.760 --> 00:43:50.680
What we want to do is rule out as many
of these as soon as possible.

637
00:43:50.800 --> 00:43:53.000
You're all going to
follow Anomie on Twitter.

638
00:43:53.080 --> 00:43:54.080
If Anomie is active

639
00:43:54.160 --> 00:43:56.840
and you can see your suspect's
not on a computer or on a phone.

640
00:43:57.080 --> 00:43:58.120
we can rule them out.

641
00:43:58.200 --> 00:44:01.040
- How often does Anomie tweet?
- Five or six times a day.

642
00:44:01.120 --> 00:44:03.320
More if they get into an argument.

643
00:44:03.400 --> 00:44:05.760
We should also sign up for Drek's game.

644
00:44:05.840 --> 00:44:07.360
Anomie's on there all the time.

645
00:44:08.200 --> 00:44:10.840
My ex used to get dead excited
when she was talking to him.

646
00:44:10.960 --> 00:44:12.480
like she'd met the Pope
or something.

647
00:44:12.640 --> 00:44:13.960
It was ridiculous.

648
00:44:17.440 --> 00:44:20.600
<i>Drek says no new players.</i>

649
00:44:22.160 --> 00:44:24.280
Maybe they're worried about
the police sniffing about.

650
00:44:24.360 --> 00:44:26.800
Murphy mentioned the Halvening
might have used the game

651
00:44:26.880 --> 00:44:29.600
to stir up hate
against Edie. so yeah.

652
00:44:31.240 --> 00:44:34.840
Is there a chance your ex
might let us use her login?

653
00:44:35.600 --> 00:44:38.880
Oh. we've not spoken for.
like. a year.

654
00:44:39.760 --> 00:44:42.160
Yeah. the relationship ended
with a lot of daytime sex.

655
00:44:42.200 --> 00:44:44.000
only I wasn't the one
having it with her.

656
00:44:44.080 --> 00:44:46.080
Oh. sorry.
Forget I asked.

657
00:44:46.880 --> 00:44:48.160
Twitter it is.

658
00:44:48.280 --> 00:44:50.360
Barclay. you're on the fiancé.
Phillip Ormond.

659
00:44:50.440 --> 00:44:53.360
He teaches in Gospel Oak
and lives in Finchley.

660
00:44:53.760 --> 00:44:56.200
Midge. you're on Katya Upcott.

661
00:44:56.440 --> 00:44:58.240
I'm going to be watching Wally.

662
00:45:50.560 --> 00:45:53.600
I'm not being funny. but you should try
and look like that more often.

663
00:45:54.640 --> 00:45:58.600
Yeah. Jessica is anxious about people
thinking she's a corporate sellout.

664
00:45:58.840 --> 00:46:00.880
Jessica could be working for Satan

665
00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:03.680
and most boys won't give a monkey's
with her looking like you do.

666
00:46:04.560 --> 00:46:07.520
Before you go. can you
take a look at the rota?

667
00:46:07.600 --> 00:46:10.360
I've got you down
for 60 hours this week.

668
00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:12.760
Yeah. I know.
We need to find more people.

669
00:46:14.440 --> 00:46:15.440
See you.

670
00:46:18.600 --> 00:46:22.200
How's she going to find a boyfriend
if she never stops working?

671
00:46:22.280 --> 00:46:24.160
Maybe she's shagging Strike.

672
00:46:24.440 --> 00:46:26.400
She's got more sense than that.

673
00:46:27.520 --> 00:46:29.240
Here I am in Regent's Park

674
00:46:29.360 --> 00:46:31.880
asking people what they like to eat for
dinner on a Friday night.

675
00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:33.800
Here. I've got a good one here
with this geezer here.

676
00:46:33.920 --> 00:46:35.880
Got one here now.
Excuse me. mate.

677
00:46:36.200 --> 00:46:38.440
Excuse me. mate...

678
00:46:38.520 --> 00:46:40.040
Want to talk about it? No?

679
00:46:40.120 --> 00:46:41.200
- Barclay.
- Do you speak English?

680
00:46:41.240 --> 00:46:43.200
I've got eyes on Edie's fiancé.

681
00:46:43.880 --> 00:46:45.240
He's glued to his phone.

682
00:46:46.520 --> 00:46:48.360
Nothing happening
in Anomie's Twitter.

683
00:46:48.600 --> 00:46:49.880
You're all set up then?

684
00:46:49.960 --> 00:46:52.920
<i>Aye. I'm using the account I used to</i>
<i>have that's still got a few followers.</i>

685
00:46:53.000 --> 00:46:54.560
Bit less sus than
a new one. eh?

686
00:46:54.640 --> 00:46:56.960
<i>So long as it doesn't have</i>
<i>your name on it.</i>

687
00:46:57.560 --> 00:46:59.200
Username's Tartan Rizla.

688
00:47:00.280 --> 00:47:02.360
<i>- You're a class act. Barclay.</i>
<i>- Right. I'm off.</i>

689
00:47:02.480 --> 00:47:03.920
Yeah.
See you.

690
00:47:04.040 --> 00:47:05.800
- I'm from California.
- Oh. all right.

691
00:47:05.880 --> 00:47:08.800
- Do you like the food here?
- Yeah. It's OK.

692
00:47:09.400 --> 00:47:10.640
You like noodles?

693
00:47:11.280 --> 00:47:12.680
- What?
- Noodles!

